PN,38601
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FThe Home Office acted unlawfully when
OL,8,Fdeciding to use a former military
OL,9,Ftraining camp as accommodation for
OL,10,Fasylum seekers, the High Court has
OL,11,Fbeen told.
OL,13,FCrowborough Shield, a community
OL,14,Finterest company, is taking legal
OL,15,Faction against the department over its
OL,16,FJanuary decision to proceed with plans
OL,17,Fto house up to 540 men at the site in
OL,18,Fthe East Sussex town.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FThe move followed Labour's pledge to
OL,8,Fuse former military barracks as
OL,9,Faccommodation for asylum seekers, in a
OL,10,Fbid to end the use of hotels by the
OL,11,Fnext election.
OL,13,FBarristers for Crowborough Shield,
OL,14,Fwhich previously had a legal challenge
OL,15,Fover the use of the site thrown out in
OL,16,FFebruary, told a hearing on Tuesday
OL,17,Fthat the Home Office's decision-making
OL,18,Fprocess lacked "openness or
OL,19,Ftransparency".
OL,26,@zD@POU{D@MO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FIt is asking a judge to declare that
OL,8,Fthe department's authorisation of the
OL,9,Fsite's use was unlawful and to quash
OL,10,Fthe decision.
OL,12,FThe Home Office, as well as the
OL,13,FMinistry of Housing, Communities and
OL,14,FLocal Government, are opposing the
OL,15,Fchallenge.
OL,17,FAlex Goodman KC, for Crowborough
OL,18,FShield, said in written submissions
OL,19,Fthat the Home Office had not acted
OL,20,F"within the ambit" of its powers, or
OL,21,Fhad exercised them irrationally.
OL,26,@|D@AOU|D@RO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FHe continued that residents involved
OL,8,Fin Crowborough Shield "do not know the
OL,9,Fbasis for or the reasons" for the
OL,10,Fdepartment's decision, meaning the
OL,11,FHome Office had failed to exercise its
OL,12,Fpowers "with the degree of openness
OL,13,Frequired".
OL,15,FHe said: "The rights of individuals
OL,16,Fare not to be overridden by hole-in-
OL,17,Fthe-corner decisions or stonewall
OL,18,Fresponses to requests for information
OL,19,Fabout how decisions are being taken."
OL,26,@pD@WOUqD@YO]tD@HOUuD@IO]wD@JOU{D@eO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FHe continued that the Home Office had
OL,8,Fexercised its powers "under conditions
OL,9,Fof secrecy" which "amounts to an abuse
OL,10,Fof power and is unlawfully
OL,11,Finconsistent with the constitutional
OL,12,Fprinciple that requires the state to
OL,13,Fcommunicate the process by which
OL,14,Fdecisions affecting the rights of
OL,15,Findividuals are made".
OL,26,@pD@VOUqD@KO]qD@SOUwD@UO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FThe barrister also claimed that the
OL,8,FHome Office wrongly decided that the
OL,9,Fneed to accommodate asylum seekers
OL,10,Fconstituted an "emergency" under
OL,11,Fplanning rules, meaning it was
OL,12,Fautomatically granted permission to
OL,13,Fdevelop the site.
OL,15,FHe continued that this was "legally
OL,16,Ferroneous" and that hotels could still
OL,17,Fbe used to house asylum seekers,
OL,18,Fadding: "If the Home Office is to rely
OL,19,Fon emergency powers... then there must
OL,20,Fbe a situation of genuine emergency
OL,21,Frather than just urgency".
OL,26,@rD@POUrD@ZO]wD@\OUxD@JO]zD@IOU}D@YO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FThe department first announced that it
OL,8,Fwas considering using the site in
OL,9,FOctober last year before confirming
OL,10,Fthe move in January, with the site's
OL,11,Fuse sparking protests in the town and
OL,12,Fprompting opposition from Wealden
OL,13,FDistrict Council.
OL,15,FThe site was previously used to
OL,16,Faccommodate Afghan families evacuated
OL,17,Fduring the withdrawal from Kabul in
OL,18,F2021 while they were resettled
OL,19,Felsewhere.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FCrowborough Shield filed a legal
OL,8,Fchallenge over the move in December,
OL,9,Fbut this was dismissed in February,
OL,10,Fwith Mr Justice Mould stating that the
OL,11,Fgroup had "jumped the gun" as it was
OL,12,Ffiled before the Government decided to
OL,13,Fproceed with plans to use the site.
OL,15,FBut the judge added that the
OL,16,FGovernment's January decision was "at
OL,17,Fleast in principle" open to challenge.
OL,26,@sD@KOUsD@ZO]xD@cOUyD@SO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FJames Strachan KC, for the Home
OL,8,FOffice, said in written submissions
OL,9,Fthat Crowborough Shield's "real
OL,10,Fcomplaint is that the Home Office
OL,11,Fshould not have used the camp for
OL,12,Fasylum accommodation", but added:
OL,13,F"That is not a legitimate ground of
OL,14,Fchallenge."
OL,26,@qD@[OUtD@UO]uD@AOUvD@KO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FHe continued that the claim that the
OL,8,FHome Office had not made its decision-
OL,9,Fmaking process open to public scrutiny
OL,10,F"lacks any proper foundation", and
OL,11,Fthat the allegation that it had made
OL,12,Fits decision "under conditions of
OL,13,Fsecrecy" was "legally incoherent".
OL,15,FHe continued: "On the claimant's case,
OL,16,Fthe Home Office, and any decision-
OL,17,Fmaker, would be required to conduct a
OL,18,Frunning commentary on its internal
OL,19,Fthinking, or face challenge on the
OL,20,Fground of insufficient 'openness'.
OL,21,FThat is not the law."
OL,26,@rD@AOUrD@]O]tD@NOUuD@HO]uD@NOUuD@aO]wD@
OL,26,AOOU}D@UO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G10/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1784720908
OL,3,CHome Office unlawfully approved
OL,4,Cmilitary site housing asylum seekers,
OL,5,Ccourt told
OL,7,FThe barrister also said that the
OL,8,F"pressures on the asylum accommodation
OL,9,Fsystem are real and acute" and that
OL,10,Fhow the department decided to address
OL,11,Fthe issue is "quintessentially a
OL,12,Fpolicy matter for the Home Office".
OL,14,FHe continued that the UK's asylum
OL,15,Fsystem was facing "severe strain",
OL,16,Fwith over 400,000 claims lodged since
OL,17,F2021 and around 112,000 people
OL,18,Fcurrently receiving state-funded
OL,19,Fsupport, the majority of whom are in
OL,20,Fasylum accommodation.
OL,26,@pD@AOUqD@ZO]sD@NOUtD@bO]wD@SOUwD@aO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/12
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
